      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SCOTT WEDNESDAY (5) doesn't win out of turn. Finished in the money last time though when third (19.64) at Bulli. Form at the trip sound including five wins. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. One of the contenders. STOP IT ZIPPER (7) sailed across from an outside draw and gave a sight, holding on for second and beaten 1.3 lengths (23.01) at this track in a Grade 5 over 400m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Must be included in calculations. AUSSIE BELL (2) finished well back at this track last time when a 16 length eighth (23.72) but recorded best time of the card when winning four back. The form from his last run stacks up well. Likely to play a prominent role. HUMBLE SMILES (3) is likely to have admirers.",
